  "texts": [
    "It may be beneficial to discuss the need for standardized frameworks or benchmarks that could provide a more systematic approach to evaluate and address biases in AI models.",
    "An even less concrete type of requests are those related to the generation of toxic, harmful, hateful, or hallucinated content.",
    "These phenomena are difficult to define in many cases because of cultural differences, the use of humor and sarcasm, the importance of context, etc.",
    "Methods that deal with these issues are often based on further fine-tuning and input and output manipulation, and therefore only provide at most weak guarantees of unlearning.",
    "For toxic and hateful content, evaluation can be carried out leveraging other LLMs such as HateBERT."
  ],
